README
======

This is a simple wall avoider robot.
Using the simple.cfg example provided by Stage it should use the front lasers to detect 
any walls.  Once the walls are within 1 meter it will rotate one direction only.


SET UP
====

The example has been tested to work on the simple world provided with Stage.
To use this demo run the erlang shell in this directory or with the KERL modules in a 
directory visible to erlang.
Run Player on the local machines or refer to the documention on how to set rih:init to 
locate Player on a remote machine.


BUILD
====

Run 'make' in the shell to compile


USAGE
=====

To run the demo in the erlang shell type

> avoid:demo().

Enjoy


